{"type":"text","timestamp":1775893813715,"sessionID":"ses_2847f24caffeU2hNyOZ4x5EBWx","part":{"id":"prt_d7b850be90010PM6MErLF387pM","messageID":"msg_d7b84f9b3001Iue2fMIy7osg7K","sessionID":"ses_2847f24caffeU2hNyOZ4x5EBWx","type":"text","text":"I've successfully created the design.md file with a comprehensive technical implementation design for AR-039 — Go unit tests (router/store/picod). The document includes:\n\n## Key Sections Covered:\n\n1. **Overview & Goals** - Clear objectives for comprehensive unit testing\n2. **Architecture** - Module structure and responsibilities for router, store, and picod\n3. **Data Structures** - Core types and error handling for each module\n4. **API Contracts** - HTTP endpoints and internal interfaces\n5. **Error Handling** - Error hierarchy and handling strategies\n6. **Testing Strategy** - Comprehensive approach including:\n   - Test organization structure\n   - Testing frameworks (testing, testify, httptest, miniredis)\n   - Coverage targets (router ≥80%, store ≥85%, picod ≥75%)\n   - Test classifications (unit, integration, table-driven)\n   - Mock strategies and helper functions\n   - Specific test scenarios for each module\n7. **Implementation Plan** - Three-phase approach with priorities\n8. **Dependencies** - Testing and runtime dependencies\n9. **Performance Considerations** - Optimization and benchmarking\n10. **Documentation & Maintenance** - Best practices and guidelines\n\nThe design follows Go testing best practices and provides a complete roadmap for implementing comprehensive unit tests across all three modules.","time":{"start":1775893813714,"end":1775893813714}}}
